No rain for the past 30 days.
Personal visit.  There was 3.1" of rain on 6/11/86.
There had been 5.5" of rain since 9/13.
There has been 2.5" of rain since last report.  Freeze up on 11/11/1986.
2.1" rain since last report- white caps.
Partly cloudy and 0.5" of rain since the last reading.
No rain since last report- lake level reading on 8/21 was 5.16.
Rained 2.1" since last report- Dissolved Oxygen is 19 parts per million.
Rained 1.1" since last report- lake level on 10/10 was 4.89- air temp. 40 F.
Rained .5' since last reading- final report for the year.
.8" rain- swimmer's itch- fish die off.
2.7" rain since last report- lots of geese and ducks on lake.
1.2" rain  since last report- dam area iced.
Partly cloudy- temperature in the 70's.  13 parts per million of dissolved oxygen in the water.
Cloudy- windy. Finally found the deep hole! Son's depth/fish finder.
Nice 70 degree day- mild breezes. Eric Tweed was my "find the deep hole" helper.
First attempt at temperature failed as battery in thermometer unit was dead. Went back at 2pm and got it! Saw a bald eagle flying over head. Sunny and hot but storm clouds gathering.
Sunny day with some clouds- calm lake.
Sunny with light clouds- windy with waves
Overcast day- water level high. Earl Tweed was my boat driver.
Beautiful day- few clouds and nice breeze.

column1: After the "tornado" of 7/20/19- homes on the south side of the lake are still dealing with downed trees- including trees in the water.
